      <para id="id1170656236094">Now complete the sentences below by writing the correct ‘building’ words in the space provided.</para>
      <para id="id1170651904944">1. _______________is the most famous prehistoric monument of standing stones and is found on Salisbury Plain in England.</para>
      <para id="id1170642139325">2. The ___________________was built for the 1889 Paris Exhibition to commemorate the 100<sup>th</sup> anniversary of the start of the French Revolution.</para>
      <para id="id1170656231352">3. Manhattan Island in New York City has more _____________than any other city section in the world.</para>
      <para id="id1170657606329">4. From toe to torch the ____________________ is 46 m tall and beneath her flowing robes is a steel frame designed by Gustav Eiffel.</para>
